touch docs/.nojekyll
git add docs/.nojekyll
git commit -m "Disable Jekyll processing"
git push
```

**However** — this means your `.md` files (like `privacy-policy.md`) will no longer be rendered as HTML. You'd need to either convert them to `.html` or use a different approach.

**Option B: Wrap the offending code in `raw` tags (keeps Jekyll working)**

In `docs/superpowers/plans/2026-03-12-phase1-solo-swipe-mvp.md`, find any code blocks that contain `{{ }}` syntax and wrap them with Liquid raw tags:
```
{% raw %}
{{ headerShown: false, contentStyle: { backgroundColor: colors.background } }}
{% endraw %}
